      "title": "Introduction: The Breath of Revelation",
      "content": "“This is eternal life, that they may know you, the only true God, and Jesus Christ whom you have sent. » — John 17:3\n\nThere is in the heart of every believer a silent thirst: that of knowing God. Not only with intelligence, but with the mind, with the heart, with all of one’s life. GYNOSKO is born from this thirst. It is not simply a teaching book, but a path of revelation, an interior journey towards the living person of God.\n\nThis book is what I wish I had in my hands when I received Christ. When I embarked on this spiritual path, full of questions, full of doubts, with few answers. It is a collection of simple but profound truths, of essential revelations that I would have wanted to hear from my first steps in faith.\n\nThrough these pages, I pray that you will enter into a deeper knowledge of God—a living, experiential knowledge, one that transforms, enlightens, heals, and strengthens.\n\nBut I didn’t do this trip alone. And I can't start this book without saying thank you.\n\nThanks to my father, who always believed in me, who was a pillar of strength and love every step of the way.\n\nThanks to mom Lili N’zola and mom Dordette, who were lights in my darkness. In my most painful moments, they were able to lift me up, remind me that God had not abandoned me, and that he still believed in me.\n\nThank you to Pastor Marc Cheyns, for his trust, for the opportunity he gave me to reveal what God had placed in me. Through his kind gaze, he was a trigger in this mission.\n\nThanks to my brother Jordy Voluzolo — more than a friend, a true companion in battle, a brother given by God to walk alongside me through the highs and lows.\n\nThanks to Anne Hermance Tacka and Hien Emmanuel Watil. You have been true brothers and sisters since my beginnings. You supported me, inspired me, and encouraged me. Your love and faith accompanied me when I was just a spiritual child, and you became lifelong companions.\n\nThanks also to Mamane Doumbia. You are for me a gift from God, an exceptional, precious, extraordinary person. Your support, your presence, your heart were for me a living testimony of God’s love. You are one of those rare people that the Lord places on our path to remind us that we are never alone. Thank you for existing.\n\nFinally, thank you to a ministry that has deeply impacted and shaped me: Christ Embassy, ​​the ministry of Pastor Chris Oyakhilome. Through his teachings, I was formed, awakened, led to a deeper love for the Word and presence of God.\n\nI am Ange Emmanuel Kouamé, a man whom the grace of God has seized, raised, shaped. And if this book can take you, too, closer to his heart, then it will have accomplished its goal.\n\nWalk with me, reader. No behind me. But alongside, on this path where the knowledge of God becomes life, light and interior fire.",
