      "title": "Christianity and the Essence of the Word",
      "content": "“If you continue in my word, you are truly my disciples; you will know the truth, and the truth will set you free. » – John 8:31-32\n\n1. What is Christianity…really?\n\nThe word “Christianity” is often misunderstood.\nSome think it is one religion among others.\nOthers associate it with a culture, with church buildings, with crosses, with rites or with the history of Europe.\nBut in reality, Christianity was not invented by men. It's not a tradition.\nIt is a divine revelation, born from a living being: Jesus Christ.\n\nOriginally, there was only one message: \nChrist is alive.\n\nJesus, the Son of God manifested in flesh, came to reveal the heart of the Father, and bring us into a direct relationship with God.\n\n2. The heart of the message: a relationship, not a religion\n\nThe word “Christianity” comes from the word “Christ”, which means “anointed”, “sent from God” and the word “Ism” which means ideology, message, teaching or doctrine.\nChristianity is the ideology or message of Christ.\nTo be a Christian is therefore to follow Christ, to think like Him, to love like Him, to live like Him.\n\nIt is not a question of label, but of transformed nature.\n\nA genuine Christian is not someone who just goes to church.\nIt is someone who knows Jesus personally, who abides in his word, and who lives by it.\n\n3. Abiding in the Word: what does that mean?\n\nJesus says in John 8:31:\n\n“If you continue in my word, you are truly my disciples. »\n\n“To remain” is:\n    • Stay connected to his words in everyday life;\n    • Meditate, understand and apply what He taught;\n    • Make his words a foundation, a refuge, a light.\n\nIn other words: live immersed in the Gospel.\n\nAnd Jesus continues:\n\n“You will know the truth, and the truth will set you free. »\n\n4. The truth liberates: but from what?\n\nMany believe that freedom means “doing what you want.”\nBut according to Jesus, true freedom is the ability to live in the light, outside of lies, outside of the slavery of sin, fear, doubt, ignorance.\n\nWhen you remain in his Word:\n    • You see life as God sees it;\n    • You understand who you really are;\n    • You are liberated internally.\n\n5. A living Word, not just written\n\nThe Word of God is not just a text.\nIt is a living voice, a spirit, a divine force.\n\nIt has three dimensions:\n    1. Written (logos) – What you read in the Bible;\n    2. Revealed (rhema) – What God shows you in a specific moment;\n    3. Living (Christ) – Jesus himself, the Word incarnate.\n\n6. The role of the Holy Spirit\n\nThe Bible is not an intellectual manual:\n\nWithout the Holy Spirit, you can read without ever hearing God.\n\nIt is the Spirit who:\n    • Gives understanding;\n    • Open the eyes of the heart;\n    • Transform what you read into living truth.\n\n7. Why you need to be taught\n\nGod uses anointed men and women (teachers, pastors, prophets, etc.) to:\n    • Help you better understand the Word;\n    • Avoid mistakes and confusion;\n    • Bring you higher in the knowledge of God.\n\nBut above all, it is the Spirit who confirms everything in your heart.",
