      "title": "The Living Word: Source of Transformation",
      "content": "“Your word is a lamp to my feet, and a light to my path. » —Psalm 119:105\n\n1. More than a text: divine energy\n\nThe Word of God is not just information.\nIt is a creative force.\nGod created the universe by His Word. And He recreates your life through His Word.\n\n2. The three dimensions of the Word (Logos, Rhema, Christ)\n\n    • Logos: The written, stable, eternal Word. It's the Bible.\n    • Rhema: The revealed Word, the one that God speaks to you now, in your heart. She becomes alive for you.\n    • Christ: The Incarnate Word. Jesus is the perfect manifestation of everything God has said.\n\n3. How does the Word transform?\n\nTransformation doesn’t come from speed reading.\nIt comes from meditation.\n\n“Meditate”, in Hebrew (Hagah), means to murmur, to ruminate, to speak in a low voice.\nIt’s getting the Word from your eyes to your heart, and from your heart to your mouth.\n\n4. The stages of transformation:\n    1. Information: You read.\n    2. Revelation: You understand by the Spirit.\n    3. Conviction: The truth grips you.\n    4. Manifestation: Your life changes.\n\n5. The power of the statement\n\nGod says, and it happens.\nAs a child of God, you are called to declare what God says about your life.\n\nWhen you declare the Word:\n    • You chase away darkness;\n    • You install the truth;\n    • You transform your atmosphere.\n\n6. The Word as food\n\nJesus said: “Man will not live by bread alone…”\nYour mind needs to eat every day.\nIf you don't read, your mind weakens.\nIf you meditate, your mind becomes strong, unshakable.\n\n7. Conclusion of the chapter\n\nThe Word is your weapon, your bread, your light.\nDon't treat her lightly.\nMake her your priority, and she will make you a spiritual giant.",
