      "content": "“For the word of God is living and effective, sharper than any two-edged sword…” — Hebrews 4:12\n\n1. The Supreme Authority\n\nIn a kingdom, the king's word is law.\nIn the Kingdom of God, His Word is the supreme authority. She is above circumstances, above feelings, above human opinions.\n\n2. Lively and Effective\n\nThe Word is not dead. She acts.\nWhen she walks into a situation, she starts working.\nIt heals hearts, it breaks chains, it enlightens choices.\n\n3. The Sword of the Spirit\n\nIn the armor of God (Ephesians 6), the Word is the only offensive weapon.\nIt is with it that you repel the enemy.\nJesus defeated Satan in the desert by saying, “It is written.”\n\n4. The Infallibility of the Word\n\nHeaven and earth will pass away, but His Word will not pass away.\nGod is not a man to lie.\nIf He said it, He will do it.\n\n5. Submission to the Word\n\nThe authority of the Word only works in your life if you submit to it.\nObeying the Word is building on rock.\nTo ignore the Word is to build on sand.\n\n6. The Power of Faith\n\nThe Word produces faith. “Faith comes by hearing…”\nThe more you immerse yourself in the Word, the more your faith grows.\nAnd with faith you move mountains.\n\n7. Conclusion\n\nDon't argue with the Word, proclaim it.\nDon’t just analyze it, live it.\nShe is your strength and your victory.",
