      "title": "The Word: Seed and Bread of Life",
      "content": "“You have been born again, not of corruptible seed, but of incorruptible seed, by the word of God, which lives and abides forever. » — 1 Peter 1:23\n\n1. The Incorruptible Seed\n\nYour new birth does not come from human effort.\nIt comes from the Word received in your heart like a seed.\nA seed contains the entire life of the plant.\nThe Word contains the whole life of God.\n\n2. The Ground of your Heart\n\nJesus taught the parable of the sower.\nThe Word is the same for everyone, but the result depends on the soil.\n    • The side of the road (indifference)\n    • Stony ground (lack of depth)\n    • Thorns (worries of the world)\n    • The good earth (open and obedient heart)\n\n3. The Bread of Life\n\nThe Word is your daily food.\nYou don't eat once for your whole life.\nWe eat every day to have strength.\n\n4. Spiritual Growth\n\nAs a baby needs milk, the new Christian needs the spiritual milk of the Word.\nThen, he grew towards solid food.\nWithout Word, there is no growth.\n\n5. The Abiding Word\n\nEverything physical ages and dies.\nBut what God said remains true forever.\nCling to the eternal.\n\n6. Bear Fruit\n\nThe purpose of a seed is to bear fruit.\nThe Word in you must produce love, joy, peace, holiness.\n\n7. Conclusion\n\nTake care of the seed in your heart.\nFeed yourself on the bread from heaven.\nAnd you will see a magnificent harvest in your life.",
