      "content": "“Is not my word like fire, says the LORD, and like a hammer that breaks rock? » — Jeremiah 23:29\n\n1. The Fire that Purifies\n\nThe Word of God is fire.\nIt burns impurities, false reasoning, bad habits.\nIt also warms the cold heart and gives zeal.\n\n2. The Hammer that Breaks\n\nThe human heart can sometimes be as hard as a rock.\nPride, unbelief, tradition can block God.\nThe Word acts like a hammer that breaks down these resistances.\n\n3. Breaking Mental Fortresses\n\nWe all have ways of thinking inherited from our past or culture.\nThe Word comes to demolish these fortresses to install the mind of Christ.\n\n4. An Inner Fire\n\nJeremiah said the Word was like a consuming fire locked in his bones.\nWhen you have the Word in you, you cannot remain passive.\nIt pushes you to bear witness, to act, to love.\n\n5. The Word that Judges\n\nShe discerns the intentions of the heart.\nIt shows us the truth about ourselves, without filter.\n\n6. The Power of Truth\n\nThe fire of the Word destroys the lies of the enemy.\nThe hammer of the Word crushes the obstacles in your path.\n\n7. Conclusion\n\nLet the fire of God burn you.\nLet the hammer of God shape you.\nHis Word will make you pure and strong.",
