      "content": "“Revive me according to your word!” » —Psalm 119:25\n\n1. What is a Revival?\n\nWaking up is not just a collective emotion.\nIt is the return of the heart to the Word of God.\nThis is when the truth becomes more real than our problems.\n\n2. The Word: Seed of Revival\n\nEvery great revival in history began with a rediscovery of the Bible.\nWhen God's people begin to read and obey again, life returns.\n\n3. Get out of Drowsiness\n\nYou can be a Christian and still be spiritually asleep.\nThe Word is the morning awakening of the soul.\nIt reminds us of our identity and our mission.\n\n4. Thirst for God\n\nThe Word creates a thirst for His presence.\nThe more we eat, the more we want.\nIt is this hunger that attracts the glory of God.\n\n5. Obedience and Anointing\n\nThe Holy Spirit honors His Word.\nWhen we put the Word into practice, the anointing flows.\nRevival is God acting through a Word believed and lived.\n\n6. A Personal Awakening\n\nDon’t wait for a church event.\nWaking up begins in your room, with your Bible open.\nLet the Word revive you today.\n\n7. Conclusion\n\nThe world needs awakened Christians.\nAnd the only path to awakening is the path of the Word.\nOpen your heart, and let life flow.",
