      "content": "“Blessed are those who hear the word of God and keep it! » — Luke 11:28\n\n1. Listen and Keep\n\nThere is a difference between hearing a sound and retaining an instruction.\nTo keep the Word is to protect it in your heart like a treasure.\nIt’s not letting it fly away at the first wind of difficulty.\n\n2. Wisdom in Action\n\nWisdom is not knowing many things.\nIt’s knowing what to do with what you know.\nBuilding your life on the Word is like the prudent man who builds on the rock.\n\n3. Light for Everyday Life\n\nThe Word not only guides our big decisions.\nIt guides our words, our reactions, our relationships, our work.\nShe is the lamp that illuminates every step.\n\n4. Resist the World\n\nThe world bombards us with philosophies contrary to God.\nThe Word is our filter.\nIf it's not in the Word, it's not for us.\n\n5. The Peace of Obedience\n\nThere is great peace in knowing that we are in the will of God.\nThis peace comes when we walk according to His principles.\n\n6. A Life of Testimony\n\nWhen you walk according to the Word, you become a living letter.\nPeople see the difference.\nYour behavior speaks louder than your words.\n\n7. Conclusion\n\nDon't just be a forgotten listener.\nBe a faithful practitioner.\nYour life will be strong, beautiful and blessed.",
